Lamb shanks are a delectable recipe to make when you have the extra time. Its speciality is how much flavour you can add to the meat, sauce and the extra flavour from braising the meat. This recipe will have you in MasterChef mode but with pantry shortcuts. Inspired by an Italian style sauce, the tomato ragout, a highly seasoned dish of small pieces of meat stewed with vegetables. Traditionally done with duck in red wine, this recipe is French cut lam shanks which you can ask your butcher to do. ALSO READ: Jamie Oliver’s easy risotto recipe to try this weekend Ingredients Method  For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.